description:
Red Raid!

It's the Marines in action, when Sgt. Rock Murdock, the fighting gyrene, and his pal PFC Scuttlebutt Stacy meet a red patrol out on a... Red Raid!

Invasion!

The ships came over the horizon toward Iwo Jima, and on their decks waited the Fifth Amphibious Corps... United States Marines! This was the day they had waited for! Iwo Jima lay before them, a small island 5 miles long and less than 2 miles wide, every inch fortified and mined by the Japs... an island that many thought couldn't be taken by direct invasion...

Corporal's War (Text Only Story)

You're In The Marines

Today, Top Sergeant Pat Brady is a Drill Instructor at the United States Marine Corps recruit depot on Parris Island, South Caroline! There are six stripes on his sleeve now, and he's know as "Boot-Camp" Brady... the gyrene who makes the Marines!

Mission Accomplished

The three Marine pilots reconnoitered the island! It was small, but crawling with Japs and installations! Three Marines on a routine flight... and though they didn't know it then, their job was just beginning, the kind of job a Marine likes... rought, and almost impossible...
name: Red Raid

description:
FINAL ROBBY BEVARD/SHIDOSHI ISSUE

175 MILESTONE ISSUE!

It is a comic book rule: Whenever a series hits a multiple of 25, it's time to celebrate! Featuring an awesome ensemble cover by series creator Ben Dunn and a bevy of special NHS extras inside!

After 10 years & 100 issues, Robby Bevard ends his NHSrun with the final issue of the Shidoshi story arc begun in issue 130!

In the wake of Shidoshi lord Yuudai's fatal defeat, life goes on for Red Ninja Ricky Feeple, his family and friends. What happens next? Vengeance, betrayal, love, legendary monsters, fond reunions, sad resolutions, satisfaction, death, life...and what the next generation will bring. And musicals!

description: "What is the use of a book," thought Alice, "without pictures or conversations!" Following up on the success of The Complete Dracula, and Sherlock Holmes, Dynamite presents The Complete Alice In Wonderland. For the first time ever Lewis Carroll's classics, Alice's Adventures in Wonderland and Through the Looking-Glass with "The Wasp in a Wig," the "lost chapter" (from the Looking-Glass) are adapted into one complete tale. In this All Ages adaptation, writers John Reppion and Leah Moore are joined by Erica Awano for a 4 issue adventure down the rabbit hole! This full color series features a massive 40 pages of story and art per issue, all under covers by John Cassaday, who supplies a unique die-cut design for the first issue that is sure to enthrall young and old. Moore and Reppion also provide bonus material such as script pages, annotations and samplings of the original text by Lewis Carroll.
